            <h1 style="font-size:42px;line-height:52px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:8px;margin-right:0;margin-left:0;padding-top:0;padding-bottom:0;padding-right:0;padding-left:0;" >
              Reversing Diabetes
            </h1>
              <table width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
                <tr>
                  <td width="370" valign="top" align="left" style="padding-right:20px;border-right-width:1px;border-right-style:dashed;border-right-color:#ddd;" >
                    <p style="font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:12px;" >Dear Lifestyle Club Member,</p>
                    <p style="margin-bottom:12px;" ><p>
	Diabetes! The word strikes fear to more than 25 million Americans who have it! In its tracks lie miserable cases of blindness, heart attacks, kidney disease, painful neuropathy, and even dementia. Diabetes can shorten the lifespan by 12 to 14 years. This is sad when science has shown that most of these cases need never exist. The &ldquo;western&rdquo; lifestyle is the main culprit.</p>
<p>
	Results from a study of more than 42000 US men show that a &ldquo;western&rdquo; diet—one that encompasses red meat, high-fat dairy products, processed and refined foods like French fries, refined grains, sweets and desserts—is associated with a substantial increase in type 2 diabetes (60%). Add to that other lifestyle indiscretions and the risk increases by nearly 80 percent.</p>
<p>
	Following the NEWSTART plan will dramatically decrease your risk, and help reverse existing diabetes. In this issue, you&rsquo;ll find a goldmine of facts and recipes to help you begin your NEW START today. We hope you enjoy!</p>
<p>
	All the best,</p>
<p>
	The NEWSTART Lifestyle Club Team</p>
<p>
	P.S. Start by calculating your health score and discover your risk for diabetes <a class="view-more-link" href="http://newsletter.foxepractice.com/t/r/l/iyikdlt/l/i/" style="text-decoration:none;color:#87A621;" >here</a>.</p>
</p>
                    
                        <div style="font-size:14px;font-weight:600;padding-top:2px;padding-bottom:2px;padding-right:0;padding-left:8px;margin-top:12px;color:white;letter-spacing:normal;-webkit-border-radius:2px;-moz-border-radius:2px;-o-border-radius:2px;border-radius:2px;background-color:#87A922;background-image:url(http://i4.createsend1.com/ti/r/35/920/947/085545/csimport/icon-small-resources_3.png);background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:330px 50%;background-attachment:scroll;margin-bottom:10px;" ><a href="http://newsletter.foxepractice.com/t/r/l/iyikdlt/l/d/" title="Featured Video" style="color:#fff;text-decoration:none;" >Featured Video</a></div>
                        <h2 style="margin-bottom:6px;line-height:1.2;" >
                          <a name="toc_item_0" style="text-decoration:none;" ></a><a class="resource-link" href="http://newsletter.foxepractice.com/t/r/l/iyikdlt/l/h/" style="text-decoration:none;color:#000;" >Reversing Diabetes</a>
                        </h2>
                        <h3 style="font-size:16px;margin-top:6px;" >By <a class="author-link" href="http://newsletter.foxepractice.com/t/r/l/iyikdlt/l/k/" style="text-decoration:none;color:#000;" >Milton Teske</a></h3>
                        <div style="background-color:transparent;background-image:url(http://i5.createsend1.com/ti/r/35/920/947/085545/csimport/email-video-frame_4.png);background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:top left;background-attachment:scroll;width:347px;height:206px;padding-top:13px;padding-bottom:0;padding-right:0;padding-left:13px;" >
                          <a href="http://newsletter.foxepractice.com/t/r/l/iyikdlt/l/u/" style="text-decoration:none;" ><img width="334" label="Video Image" src="http://i3.createsend1.com/ei/r/CD/2F5/CD3/csimport/sample-video.150506.jpg" height="186" /></a>
                        </div>
                        <p style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:10px;font-size:16px;" >
                          <p>
	In this updated Reversing Diabetes, Dr. Milton Teske explains how Type 2 diabetes works in simple terms that anyone can understand. Once you understand it, the answers to reversing diabetes become clear. Dr. Teske explains how you can begin to prevent or reverse diabetes today with simple lifestyle changes.</p>
                        </p>
