                        <div style="font-size:14px;font-weight:600;padding-top:2px;padding-bottom:2px;padding-right:0;padding-left:8px;margin-top:12px;color:white;letter-spacing:normal;-webkit-border-radius:2px;-moz-border-radius:2px;-o-border-radius:2px;border-radius:2px;background-color:#87A922;background-image:url(http://i4.createsend1.com/ti/r/35/920/947/085545/csimport/icon-small-resources_3.png);background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:330px 50%;background-attachment:scroll;margin-bottom:10px;" ><a href="http://newsletter.foxepractice.com/t/r/l/iyikdlt/l/n/" title="Featured Article" style="color:#fff;text-decoration:none;" >Featured Article</a></div>
                        <h2 style="margin-bottom:6px;line-height:1.2;" >
                          <a name="toc_item_1" style="text-decoration:none;" ></a><a class="resource-link" href="http://newsletter.foxepractice.com/t/r/l/iyikdlt/l/p/" style="text-decoration:none;color:#000;" > The Winning Diet for Type 2 Diabetes </a>
                        </h2>
                        <h3 style="font-size:16px;margin-top:6px;" >By <a class="author-link" href="http://newsletter.foxepractice.com/t/r/l/iyikdlt/l/x/" style="text-decoration:none;color:#000;" >Elizabeth Hall</a></h3>
                        <div style="background-color:transparent;background-image:url(http://i5.createsend1.com/ti/r/35/920/947/085545/csimport/email-video-frame_4.png);background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:top left;background-attachment:scroll;width:347px;height:206px;padding-top:13px;padding-bottom:0;padding-right:0;padding-left:13px;" >
                          <a href="http://newsletter.foxepractice.com/t/r/l/iyikdlt/l/m/" style="text-decoration:none;" ><img width="334" label="Article Image" src="http://i4.createsend1.com/ei/r/CD/2F5/CD3/csimport/woman_with_oranges.151200.jpg" height="187" /></a>
                        </div>
                        <p style="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:10px;font-size:16px;" >
                          <p>
	Vegetarian and vegan diets offer significant benefits for diabetes prevention, treatment, and reversal of type 2 diabetes,in many cases. In observational studies, individuals following vegetarian diets are about half as likely to develop diabetes, compared with non-vegetarians.1 Clinical trials show that individuals with type 2 diabetes who consume a low-fat vegan diet improve blood sugar control to a greater extent than conventional diabetes diets. Vegetarian and vegan diets also improve plasma lipid by reducing the total cholesterol, LDL (&ldquo;the bad cholesterol&rdquo;), and triglycerides. A vegan diet has been shown to reverse atherosclerosis progression when combined with exercise and stress management.</p>
                        </p>
